sql:
SELECT user_id, COUNT(*) AS total_reviews
FROM reviews
GROUP BY user_id;

SELECT total_reviews, total_compliments, engagement_score
FROM user_analytics
ORDER BY total_reviews DESC;

external_knowledge:
- Elite status is determined by the level achieved by each user, which can be gold, platinum, etc.; 
- Compliments are a measure of user engagement and can be seen as a badge of honor on the platform; 
- Distinct reviews engaged represent the variety of reviews a user has interacted with; 
- Average sentiment score is a measure of how positively or negatively a user's reviews are perceived; 
- Categories reviewed represent the variety of business categories a user has reviewed.

sql:
SELECT AVG(u.no_friends) AS average_friends_of_elite_users
   FROM users u
   INNER JOIN elite_status es ON u.user_id = es.user_id;

SELECT user_id, total_compliments
FROM user_analytics
ORDER BY total_compliments DESC;

SELECT user_id, total_reviews
FROM user_analytics
WHERE total_reviews = (SELECT MAX(total_reviews) FROM user_analytics);

SELECT total_reviews
FROM user_analytics
WHERE user_id = 'some_user_id';
